      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Validation_CheckCurrentProcessingPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to verify whether the current billing period has already been processed. It checks the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.ApplicationTimeFrame",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table to determine the current processing period and then verifies if data for this period has been processed in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "billing.AccountBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. If the data has been processed, it updates the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConEd.ConEdDataUploadStep",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table to mark the period as completed and raises an error message indicating that the data for the period has already been processed."
        }
      ]
    },
